  <facilityDescription><![CDATA[<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Restaurants &amp; Bars</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span><strong>Il Baglio</strong> is open for breakfast, lunch and dinner and offers a large buffet with Sicilian and international dishes including pizza cooked in a wood-fired oven.</p>
<p><strong>Ossi di Seppia Restaurant</strong> is located on the beach and offers refreshments and light lunches.</p>
<p><strong>Riviere</strong> is next to the pool and is perfect for a light, casual lunch.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Pools &amp; Beaches</strong></span></p>
<p>The large outdoor pool offers two swimming lanes, a children's area and plenty of sun loungers, meaning you're sure to find your ideal spot. The wide, sandy beach is 1,250 metres away from the resort and can be reached by the hotel's complimentary shuttle. You'll be well taken care of here with a restaurant, watersports and loungers.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Spa</strong></span></p>
<p>The Thalasso Wellness Centre has a heated indoor seawater pool and hydrojets, treatments and massages (local charge).</p>
<p><strong><u>Activities</u></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Watersports available at the beach </li>
<li>Outdoor fitness area</li>
<li>Children’s club and entertainment</li>
<li>Tennis and archery available at a local charge</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>]]></facilityDescription>
  <familyDescription><![CDATA[<p>Children can enjoy the play area and activities at the Mini Club, which runs for ages 6 to 12 years. The restaurants all have menus especially designed for children.</p>]]></familyDescription>
